Comment: I don‚Äôt ever believe Madden hype because it very rarely delivers. Basically just updated rosters every year. So many errors, glitches and uniform issues. As a life long Broncos fan I‚Äôve never seen the Broncos wear what Madden calls their 90s throwbacks but they got the jersey and helmet right but everything else is wrong. Every year I hope to see it corrected so I can use those 90s throwbacks which are some of my favorite uniforms ever but every year it‚Äôs still incorrect. There were a few things I liked about Madden 18 such as giving more stadiums a surrounding so it didn‚Äôt look like it was in the middle of nowhere on a field of dreams. Nonetheless, I‚Äôll probably buy Madden 19 as many of us that complain about it probably will. I play franchise a lot and one thing that drives me nuts is the scheduling. I hate playing like 5 or 6 straight home or road games during the season. This does not happen in the NFL. I wish they would just allow users to toggle between home and away games which was an option NCAA had for schedules on their game. I also wish the NFL wouldn‚Äôt have so many restrictions with Madden such as the requirement that every stadium must be full. Nothing more unrealistic than playing on the road late in the season against an 0-13 in front of a packed house. Anyways, rant over.
